The error is thrown in `platform/cli/src/scaffold.ts` at line 421-425 in the `promptForMissingArgs` function:

```typescript
if (!process.stdin.isTTY) {
  const missing = [!name && 'name', !domain && '--domain'].filter(Boolean);
  throw new ScaffoldError(
    `Missing required arguments: ${missing.join(', ')}. Provide them as flags or run interactively.`,
  );
}
```

Change to something like:
```typescript
throw new ScaffoldError(
  `Missing required arguments: ${missing.join(', ')}.\n\nUsage: opentabs plugin create <name> --domain <domain>\nExample: opentabs plugin create my-app --domain .example.com --display "My App"`,
);
```

Also check if the `create-opentabs-plugin` binary path (`platform/create-plugin/src/index.ts`) shows the same error — it uses the same scaffold function so it should get the fix automatically.
